<% content_for :title, "Checkout & Payment — Help" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Help", path: help_path },
      { label: "Checkout & Payment", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Checkout & Payment</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">How the hold timer works and what to expect during payment.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-stone-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">The Hold Timer</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            When you click <strong>Continue to Checkout</strong>, the app places a short hold on your
            selected slots. This temporarily reserves them so nobody else can book the same time while
            you complete payment.
          </p>
          <p>
            A countdown timer on the checkout page shows how much time you have left. You must complete
            payment before the timer reaches zero. If it expires, your slots are released back to open
            and you'll need to go back to the calendar and select them again.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you want to change your selection before paying, click <strong>Release Hold & Go Back</strong>
            to return to the calendar immediately.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Reviewing Your Booking</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            The checkout page shows:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
            <li>Your selected sessions with dates and start times</li>
            <li>Total cost (number of hours × hourly rate)</li>
            <li>The current Studio Agreement, which you must accept before paying</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Check the agreement box to confirm you've read and accepted the studio's terms. Each booking
            records the exact version of the terms you agreed to.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Secure Payment via Stripe</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            Clicking <strong>Confirm & Pay</strong> takes you to Stripe's secure payment page. All card
            processing happens on Stripe — the studio never sees or stores your card details.
          </p>
          <p>
            After successful payment, Stripe redirects you back to a confirmation page. Your booking is
            now locked in and appears under <strong>My Bookings</strong>.
          </p>
          <p>
            If your payment fails (e.g., card declined), the hold on your slots is released automatically
            and you can try again from the calendar. You'll receive a notification if you have them enabled.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Emails After Your Booking</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            After your payment is confirmed, you'll receive a <strong>confirmation email</strong>
            with your session date and time, the total you paid, and a link to your Stripe receipt.
          </p>
          <p>
            The day before your session, you'll also receive a <strong>reminder email</strong>
            with your session details and the studio address.
          </p>
          <p>
            A few hours after your session ends, we'll send a short <strong>follow-up email</strong>
            with a link to book your next session whenever you're ready.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
